etymologies: mid 19th century. From French aéronef kind of airship, heavier-than-air aircraft from aéro- + nef ship

definitions: A flying machine, an aircraft; specifically (a) a lighter-than-air flying machine, a balloon, especially a dirigible balloon, an airship; (b) a heavier-than-air flying machine, especially an aeroplane.

notes.text: In earlier use often as a rendering of or with reference to French use of the word. The varying denotation of the word in English partly reflects similar variation in French.
